race.description: The Royal Bangkok Sports Club Trophy Hcp (Bm65)
race.comment: EVERY HEART (11) switched from the Freedman's Sydney yard and looked a run short beaten 2.7L at Doomben. She's been freshened and carried 4kg less in this grade. She has plenty up her sleeve and won her only second up outing. This is winnable with the extra fitness. KING KRYPTOS (4) has won his last two here and keeps improving. Draws awkwardly and carries 2kg more but has decent claims again. TARPS (7) runs along and has just missed at the track her last two. Tumbles in weight and despite an outside barrier can't be ruled out. COMMAND APPROVED (3) won here this grade over a bit shorter and is back on track. He also deserves plenty of consideration.
